title: Russian private army head claims forces have won control of Ukraine's Bakhmut
description: The head of Russian private army Wagner has claimed his fighters have completed the capture of eastern Ukrainian city Bakhmut, after the longest battle of the Ukraine war.

title: The F-16 fighter jets: Why they could be significant to Ukraine and when they can be delivered
description: The US has approved sending F-16 fighter jets to Ukraine to enhance the country's air defence in the wake of a barrage of Russian missiles.

title: Former Wimbledon champion charged with second doping offence over biological passport
description: Two-time Grand Slam champion Simona Halep has been charged with a second doping offence over "irregularities" in her athlete biological passport.

title: Former agency bosses indicted in Brazil over death of British journalist
description: Two former agency officials have been indicted in Brazil in connection with the murder of a British freelance journalist.

title: 'A day of joy': Brittney Griner makes return to basketball after release from Russian jail
description: US basketball star Brittney Griner has returned to the court for her first professional league game since her Russian prison ordeal.
